    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-06T11:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-06T11:25:00-05:00" n="775"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d775">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1635: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-06T19:00:00+02:35"
                            >October 6, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 6—4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>115. At today’s meeting of Diplomatic Corps but without Italian Minister, it was
                    decided to request our respective Governments to bring to the attention of
                    Italian Government the fact that cities of Addis Ababa and Diredawa are open and
                    undefended. The former contains about 6,000 and the latter about 2,000 foreign
                    nationals including many women and children.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
